history.content:
Want to become a circuit design guru?  Separate yourself from the diligent hordes of students

taking ML?  Gain a skill that can get you a great job in a $25 billion industry, or a spot in a

research team?

Well c'mon down to EE140.  You'll learn how to design op-amps, temperature sensors, bandgap

reference voltage generators, analog-to-digital converters and more.  You'll design in a commercially

available process, and for the best students in the class who choose to keep working in spring, you'll

send your designs out and get chips back in time to test them in summer.

WF 11-12:30 521 Cory
